content: @ccleighton @Sflecce @fordnation @jkwan_md @DFisman @KashPrime @SharkawyMD 5/ #TTC 🚍are std 2.6 mx12 m(40’). School🚌 vary in length, some 40’, but majority are 2.6 m x 6 m mini-buses—w/ 2m physical distancing capacity of ~3 students—which is clearly impractical and uneconomical. Clearly, 😷 masking, fresh air ventilation & spacing are ALL critical.

content: @ccleighton @Sflecce @fordnation @jkwan_md @DFisman @KashPrime @SharkawyMD 4/ This insight came to me riding a #TTC 🚍in late March. It dawned on my how narrow the buses were (Doh…4 yrs w/ #TTC) and, I looked up widths…2.6m std NA 🚍width. content: @ccleighton @Sflecce @fordnation There is an easy solution, as per NYC schools, for not only school buses, but #TTC & (standard width ~2.6m wide) public transit buses—simply open sufficient windows to provide fresh air ventilation that mimics an outdoor environment—greatly lowering risk of Covid-19🦠infection.

content:
When creating the TTC, of the first 5 buses the City of Toronto tried out, a Leyland was the fifth. It wasn’t chosen. Here’s an ad from Leyland #onthisday in 1920 which exuded hope that theirs would be accepted.
.

content:
So, riding a packed transit vehicle with your huge backpack on and wondering why all of a sudden your backpack got really heavy all of a sudden?

content:
EB train pulls into Yonge.

People ready to get off. Train stops and suddenly pulls out. PA says #TTC transit control orders Yonge to be skipped.

It’s apparently due to overcrowding at Bloor-Yonge, but there was no prior warning. No contingency.

There has to be a better plan.

content:
There a few things in #Toronto more heartbreaking than waiting for a streetcar, only to find out it's been replaced by a bus.

On the streetcar
Where we all 
Furtively
Clutch and stare at our phones
As if we can

Are touching while we face each ofher
Because some human 
Thought this would be 
A good design idea 
#Toronto #TTC
